Titolo: Spore (1987 video game)

Anno: 1987

Descrizione: Spore is an action puzzle game for the Commodore 64, Commodore 16, and ZX Spectrum, released by Mastertronic in 1987. Its title screen credits Jim Baguley with writing it, although Paul Rogers claims to have written it and its unreleased sequel, Mutant Zone. The music was composed by David Whittaker.
The game includes a level editor for users to create their own maps.